<div1 type="letter">

<note type="curatorial">5</note>

<fw>Mari Sandoz<lb/>
422 Hudson Street<lb/>
New York 14, N.Y.</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>Mar 11, 1961</dateline>
<salute>Dear John Neihardt:</salute>
</opener>

<p>South Pass Pete is
Peter Decker. I think
Pete considered the item
and Black Elk's prayer
as a sort of notice that
you were here. They seldom
mention a speaker or a 
topic spoken about. That's
the way of the Chicago
corral. I don't have
any hand in this. I am not
here often, and too busy
when I am. You were

<pb/>
certainly beloved by
your audience, as
a speaker and an
artist. </p>
<p>Spring is calling
me west but I have
galley proofs to read
before I go free.</p>
<p>I do despise New York,
but I'm undisrupted
less here when the work
piles up.</p>

<closer><salute>Be nice to yourself.</salute>

<signed> 
Mari</signed></closer>

<note type="curatorial">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</note>

</div1>

